\begin{titlepage}
\vspace*{1.0in}
\begin{center}
{\bf Gauging  internal fermionic symmetries and spin 3/2 fields}
\end{center}
\begin{center} 
S.T. Love\footnote{e-mail address: love@physics.purdue.edu} \\
{\it Department of Physics\\ 
Purdue University\\
West Lafayette, IN 47907-2306}
~\\
\end{center}
\vspace{1in}
\begin{center}
{\bf Abstract}\\
Field theoretic models possessing a global internal fermionic shift symmetry are considered. When such a symmetry is realized locally, spin 3/2 fields appear naturally  as gauge fields. Implementation of the gauging procedure requires not only the usual replacement of ordinary derivatives by covariant derivatives containing the spin 3/2 fields, but also the inclusion of additional monomials. 
The Higgs mechanism and the high energy Nambu-Goldstone fermion equivalence theorem are 
explicitly demonstrated. 
\end{center}


\
